@startuml
title Optimisation Status and Result Retrieval — Read-Only Monitoring

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #EEF2FF
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #4F46E5
skinparam sequenceActorBackgroundColor #EEF2FF
skinparam sequenceActorBorderColor #4F46E5
skinparam noteBorderColor #A5B4FC
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #EEF2FF

actor "User & OEX" as Caller
participant "OGW" as OGW
participant "OSB MS" as OSB
participant "NGW" as NGW
participant "OC MS" as OCMS
database "OC MS DB" as OCDB

== Status / Result Request ==

Caller -> OGW : 1. Request optimisation\nstatus or result
OGW -> OGW : 2. Authenticate caller/session\nand derive user context

note right of OGW
User context may include tenant, claims,
roles/scopes, and entitlements.
end note

OGW -> OSB : 3. Invoke OSB MS\nmTLS + User Context JWT\ncorrelationId / traceId

OSB -> OSB : 4. Validate access to\nrequested optimisation view\nusing user context

note right of OSB
User-context-related filtering and
experience-layer authorisation are performed
by OSB MS before the request crosses NGW.

Backend OC MS decision still wins.
end note

OSB -> NGW : 5. Forward status/result request\nmTLS + OAuth2 system identity\ncorrelationId / traceId\n(no user context downstream)

note right of NGW
User context stops before/at NGW.
Downstream OC MS call uses system/service identity only.
end note

NGW -> OCMS : 6. Route GET /optimisation/{id}\nmTLS + service/system auth

note right of OCMS
OC MS authorises the calling service/system.
OC MS does not receive or depend on end-user
identity, claims, roles, or scopes.
end note

== Data Retrieval ==

OCMS -> OCDB : 7. Read runtime Optimisation\nby id
OCDB --> OCMS : Runtime record\nlifecycleStatus + result if terminal\nETag + _links

== Response ==

OCMS --> NGW : 8. Return runtime Optimisation\nlifecycleStatus\nstatusChangeDate\nresult if terminal\n_links/actions where applicable
NGW --> OSB : 9. Return response to OSB MS

OSB -> OSB : 10. Shape OptimisationDetailView\nor OptimisationSummaryView

note right of OSB
OSB may format labels and guidance for OEX,
but it must not infer terminal status locally.
Terminal state must come from OC MS.
end note

OSB --> OGW : 11. OEX-friendly status/result view\nwith backend correlation/trace details
OGW --> Caller : 12. Current lifecycle/result state

== Read-Only Boundary ==

note over OCMS
No OC MS Outbox record is written.
No worker instruction is emitted.
This is a read-only monitoring operation.
end note

@enduml
